Doc,<br><br>
I responded to a conception I had of your older posts.  I am not certain of your concept of &quot;pre-doc&quot; or &quot;post-doc&quot; but I understand the &quot;tapes&quot; concept.<br><br>
I served with the 1st Cav Div (Airmobile) at Bien Hoa Army Base from 7/69 to 3/70 in various activities.<br><br>
My Veterans of the VietNam War post here in south central PA has conducted many seminars in the local school systems.  The reception was, Quite frankly, mixed.  The students wanted answers and the teachers (non-vets) wanted out.  It was great therapy.  I have also been the recipient of PTSD counselling on an individual basis.  When I am discussing my experiences with a professional to sort out my lingering problems, I prefer those who have at least served in the military in wartime.  I am not convinced that your background would be effective in attaining an effective &quot;handle&quot; on them.<br><br>
At any rate, it is enheartening to have an open forum on the subject.<br><br>
Interested vets and others may e-mail me.<br><br>
Regards,<br><br>
Bill
